# Frontend Conventions

## Routing

- React Router v6 in `App.jsx`.
- Pages live in `src/pages/`; register new routes in `App.jsx`.
- Shared layout: `PageHeader` and `PageFooter` from `_shared.jsx`.

## Auth

- Use `useAuth()` from `context/AuthContext.jsx` for user state and auth actions.
- Authenticated API calls must include `credentials: 'include'` (cookie-based JWT).
- Login/register UI is in `AuthModal.jsx`; password reset page at `/reset-password`.

## Styling

- Add styles to `App.css` with feature-prefixed class names (e.g. `aqb-`, `rp-`, `lesson-`, `lqp-`, `modal-`).
- Match existing visual patterns: green palette (`--green`, `#3a5a40`, `#243f2b`).

## Course / lesson UX

- Quizzes appear in the sidebar under their lesson (`has_quiz` flag).
- Users take quizzes on the dedicated route: `/courses/:slug/lesson/:lessonId/quiz`.
- Do not embed the quiz under the video for regular users; admin quiz builder stays on the lesson page.
- Completed lessons show visual indicators in the sidebar (`.completed` class).

## Assets

- Remote images/fonts from `talweehacademy.com` CDN — internet required locally.

## PropTypes

- Some files use `/* eslint-disable react/prop-types */` — follow the convention of the file you edit.

## API calls

- Dev server proxies `/api` to `http://localhost:3001` — use relative paths like `/api/courses/...`.
